.tooluniverse/

# Benchmark harness — dev-only, kept locally but never tracked.
# Plugin build doesn't include skills/evals/ in dist, and .gitattributes
# already excludes it from `git archive` release tarballs.
skills/evals/

# Skill iteration / evaluation workspaces — `tooluniverse-*-workspace/`
# directories hold with-skill-vs-without-skill comparison runs produced
# by the skill evaluator. They have no SKILL.md (not real skills), match
# the sync-skills.sh `tooluniverse-*` glob accidentally, and bloat plugin/
# without ever shipping to users. Keep locally for dev, never track.
**/tooluniverse-*-workspace/

# One-off outputs from working-example scripts that write to cwd
# (e.g. ddi_working_example.py). Outputs should go to /tmp or an explicit
# --output-dir, never beside the example source.
**/DDI_report_*.md
**/*_metabolomics_report*.md

# Superseded skill source — when SKILL.md is rewritten, keep the prior
# version in git history (git log / git show) instead of beside the new
# one as SKILL_OLD.md, where it ships to users and causes confusion.
**/SKILL_OLD.md
**/SKILL_v[0-9]*.md

# Dev iteration notes that lived inside skill source: comparison
# write-ups, test feedback diaries, "fixed" twin implementations.
# Belong in git history or PR descriptions, not the shipped skill tree.
**/COMPARISON_*.md
**/*_FEEDBACK.md
**/*_implementation_fixed.py
**/*_implementation_v[0-9]*.py

# Per-user auto-memory / private session notes (never push)
memory/
MEMORY.md
CLAUDE.md

# API keys & secrets
.env
.env.local
credentials.json
*_api_key*
*_token*
